This paper proposes a novel multi-label classification model that combines Ranking Support Vector Machine (Rank-SVM) and Binary Relevance (BR) with robust low-rank learning. The paper focuses on machine learning and computer vision applications, which are typically covered by the cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of low-rank constraints to exploit high-order label correlations, which is relevant to the cs.CL and cs.IR sub-categories that deal with natural language processing and information retrieval.
